If you want the type to be `4` (i.e. bytes) then you need to send an actual JMS `BytesMessage`, e.g.:

```java
public static void sendMessage(QueueSession queueSession, MessageProducer messageProducer, String body, long expiration, String replyTo, int persistent, int priority, Map&lt;String, String&gt; propertiesMap, String CorrelationID, String typeMessage) {
    try {
         if (messageProducer == null){
            DialogsAlert.queueConnectionError.showAndWait();
         }
         Queue replyToQueue = (Queue) initialContext.lookup(&quot;dynamicQueues/&quot; + replyTo);
         messageProducer.setPriority(priority);
         messageProducer.setTimeToLive(expiration);
         messageProducer.setDeliveryMode(persistent);
         BytesMessage message = queueSession.createBytesMessage();
         message.writeBytes(body.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));
         message.setJMSReplyTo(replyToQueue);
         message.setJMSCorrelationID(CorrelationID);
         message.setJMSType(typeMessage);
         for (Map.Entry&lt;String, String&gt; property : propertiesMap.entrySet()) {
            if (!property.getKey().isEmpty()) {
               message.setStringProperty(property.getKey(), property.getValue());
            }
         }
         messageProducer.send(message);
         DialogsAlert.messageSendSuccess.showAndWait();
      } catch (JMSException | NamingException e) {
         DialogsAlert.messageSendError.showAndWait();
      }
   }
}
```
The value set using [`setJMSType`][1] is really a provider-specific value. It doesn&#39;t reflect the underlying data structure of the message which is what &quot;type&quot; refers to when looking at the web console. JMS supports the following kinds of messages:

 - [Text][2]
 - [Bytes][3]
 - [Map][4]
 - [Object][5] (not recommended)
 - [Stream][6]


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/jms/Message.html#setJMSType-java.lang.String-
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/jms/TextMessage.html
  [3]: https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/jms/BytesMessage.html
  [4]: https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/jms/MapMessage.html
  [5]: https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/jms/ObjectMessage.html
  [6]: https://docs.oracle.com/javaee/7/api/javax/jms/StreamMessage.html

